      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Some argue that segregation allowed distinct cultural groups to develop and maintain their unique traditions without outside interference, which they see as preserving valuable heritage. Furthermore, proponents claimed that separation prevented social friction and conflict by keeping different groups apart, thereby maintaining a perceived level of order. This perspective suggests that by limiting interaction, the existing social structure remained stable according to the prevailing norms of the time.",
